column5: Will be fishing Lake of the Woods outside of Morson near Dawson Island next week. Appreciate any reports on LOTW water levels, fire restrictions, fishing action etc. Thanks JT

Water levels have been rising and lake levels are at the 15% percentile. We have had rain and the fire level is low. Bass fishing has been good. Walleyes have been caught both at 6 feet and 25 feet. You'll have to figure that one out when you arrive. The lake is about 8 or 9 inches lower than it was this time last year.
Thanks Bob Looking forward to trying to figure it out Thats why they call it fishin'!
